{
  "texts": [
    "We also assume m ≥ n, as one can transpose A if necessary.",
    "Note that the semi-orthogonal low-rank factors live on Stiefel manifolds, requiring a treatment with Riemannian gradient descent (RGD).",
    "For technical simplicity, we consider a procedure that alternates between updating Θ t and (X t, Y t).",
    "At iteration t, it starts by finding Θ t with gradient descent (GD) using learning rate γ > 0, i.e.,",
    "Setting γ = 1 significantly simplifies our analysis."
  ]
}